cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with neural networks and their sensitivity to malicious perturbations. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as image classification is a common application of neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural networks are a popular tool in AI research. The paper also addresses security concerns, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of Lipschitz constants and prediction margins suggests that it could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
